Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, and abnormal urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity), suggesting impaired renal function, possibly chronic kidney disease. There is also glycosuria with low HbA1c, which may indicate renal glycosuria rather than diabetes. Lipid profile shows high LDL and low HDL, increasing cardiovascular risk. Further nephrological evaluation and assessment for underlying causes are recommended.
